00:11:49.920 --> 00:11:51.753
I'm not an absolutist
when it comes to food.

00:11:51.753 --> 00:11:54.800
I feel like you can drive
yourself nuts with food,

00:11:54.800 --> 00:11:56.067
and many people do.

00:11:56.067 --> 00:11:58.150
And I think to me the
health benefits, by the way,

00:11:58.150 --> 00:12:00.550
of exercise trump mild
to moderate obesity.

00:12:00.550 --> 00:12:02.980
I'd much rather you be mild
to moderately overweight

00:12:02.980 --> 00:12:04.810
and exercising every
day than super skinny

00:12:04.810 --> 00:12:07.420
and not exercising at all.

00:12:07.420 --> 00:12:10.630
So the concept of what drug
works for everything from some

00:12:10.630 --> 00:12:12.280
of the brain issues
I talked about,

00:12:12.280 --> 00:12:14.380
reduction in the frequency
of the common cold,

00:12:14.380 --> 00:12:16.910
reduction of blood pressure,
reduction of cholesterol

00:12:16.910 --> 00:12:20.710
levels, treatment of diabetes,
treatment and prevention

00:12:20.710 --> 00:12:22.320
of osteoarthritis
and osteoporosis,

00:12:22.320 --> 00:12:24.070
even certain types of
cancer, particularly

00:12:24.070 --> 00:12:27.670
colon cancer, which is about
40% less common in people who

00:12:27.670 --> 00:12:31.100
exercise four to five
times a week is exercise.

00:12:31.100 --> 00:12:33.930
So this is definitely
a medicine.

00:12:33.930 --> 00:12:35.680
And you can think
about it in everything

00:12:35.680 --> 00:12:37.570
from the kind of
life people live

00:12:37.570 --> 00:12:40.261
to the duration of
life people live.

00:12:40.261 --> 00:12:42.510
Every hour you put in of
exercise-- and because you're

00:12:42.510 --> 00:12:45.300
exercising, you live longer--
correlates to about five

00:12:45.300 --> 00:12:46.950
and a half hours
of life expectancy

00:12:46.950 --> 00:12:47.991
if you're going vigorous.

00:12:47.991 --> 00:12:50.530
By the way, I'm a big
fan of vigorous activity.

00:12:50.530 --> 00:12:53.000
So if you have a
half hour-- and I

00:12:53.000 --> 00:12:54.890
talk about the different
zones of exertion.

00:12:54.890 --> 00:12:57.430
Zone one is what I'm in
right now, just talking,

00:12:57.430 --> 00:12:59.230
and you could exercise and walk.

00:12:59.230 --> 00:13:01.420
Zone two is when it's a
little bit uncomfortable,

00:13:01.420 --> 00:13:03.503
and zone three is when
you're huffing and puffing,

00:13:03.503 --> 00:13:05.485
like Sunday you'll be
in zone three some.

00:13:05.485 --> 00:13:07.060
You'll be in zone
three some Sunday.

00:13:07.060 --> 00:13:10.460
So I want people to
be for their workouts

00:13:10.460 --> 00:13:14.650
about 25% in zone three, 25% in
zone two and 50% in zone one.

00:13:14.650 --> 00:13:17.405
So if you're just going for
a slow jog, that's great,

00:13:17.405 --> 00:13:19.320
or a slow walk, that's fine.

00:13:19.320 --> 00:13:23.170
But try and push your zones
up for at least a quarter

00:13:23.170 --> 00:13:25.120
of every workout up to
zone three, if you can.

00:13:25.120 --> 00:13:26.870
Not only does it help
profuse your organs,

00:13:26.870 --> 00:13:29.750
like your brain et cetera,
it's just generally much better

00:13:29.750 --> 00:13:31.250
for your heart
muscle, which is also

00:13:31.250 --> 00:13:33.740
a muscle that needs
to be exercised.

00:13:33.740 --> 00:13:37.151
And since women live longer,
exercise has very favorable--

00:13:37.151 --> 00:13:38.650
but again, it's the
intensity, which

00:13:38.650 --> 00:13:42.720
is a big piece of this, in terms
of looking at what that means.

00:13:42.720 --> 00:13:45.420
This was a big study that
was published this past year

00:13:45.420 --> 00:13:47.215
in the "British Medical
Journal" and got a lot of play

00:13:47.215 --> 00:13:47.740
in the media.

00:13:47.740 --> 00:13:50.073
It actually came out of the
week before my book came out

00:13:50.073 --> 00:13:51.710
in December, which
I didn't even know.

00:13:51.710 --> 00:13:53.600
But I was like, wow,
that was good luck.

00:13:53.600 --> 00:13:55.260
And what these guys
did is they looked

00:13:55.260 --> 00:13:58.700
at basically 16 meta-analyses,
four on exercise

00:13:58.700 --> 00:14:01.560
and 12 on drug trials,
looking at four conditions,

00:14:01.560 --> 00:14:03.510
prevention of coronary
artery disease,

00:14:03.510 --> 00:14:06.279
prevention of diabetes,
rehabilitation of stroke,

00:14:06.279 --> 00:14:07.570
and treatment of heart failure.

00:14:07.570 --> 00:14:11.060
And they compared exercise
to drugs, all right?

00:14:11.060 --> 00:14:13.040
Straight comparisons,
exercise to drugs.

00:14:13.040 --> 00:14:17.490
What they found was in about
almost 400,000 participants

00:14:17.490 --> 00:14:20.299
there was no difference
in exercise versus drug

00:14:20.299 --> 00:14:22.590
groups in the prevention of
heart disease and diabetes.

00:14:22.590 --> 00:14:24.360
What that means is that
all these people that

00:14:24.360 --> 00:14:25.735
go to their doctor,
all right, go

00:14:25.735 --> 00:14:29.460
take Crestor, Lipitor, whatever
it is as part of what you're

00:14:29.460 --> 00:14:32.260
doing in a preventive
way, exercise

00:14:32.260 --> 00:14:35.650
was just as effective with much
less cost and much less side

00:14:35.650 --> 00:14:36.150
effect.

00:14:36.150 --> 00:14:38.680
I see every week 200, 300
people in my office coming

00:14:38.680 --> 00:14:41.340
in with Lipitor or
Crestor-induced myalgia.

00:14:41.340 --> 00:14:42.550
Their muscles are super sore.

00:14:42.550 --> 00:14:44.780
Their joints get achy
because of these medicines.

00:14:44.780 --> 00:14:47.370
There is no such thing
as a perfectly safe drug.

00:14:47.370 --> 00:14:49.720
Even the Tylenol you
get at CVS or the Advil

00:14:49.720 --> 00:14:53.140
you get at the bodega around
the corner has a side effect.

00:14:53.140 --> 00:14:54.890
Now normally that
doesn't cause a problem,

00:14:54.890 --> 00:14:57.340
but there's no such thing
as a perfectly safe drug.

00:14:57.340 --> 00:15:00.055
The only drug, basically, with
no side effects is this one.

00:15:00.055 --> 00:15:01.830
And it was more
effective than medicine

00:15:01.830 --> 00:15:04.746
in the treatment of stroke
but was less effective

00:15:04.746 --> 00:15:06.620
than drugs in the
treatment of heart failure.

00:15:06.620 --> 00:15:09.060
So I'm not anti
Western medicine.

00:15:09.060 --> 00:15:11.371
I'm pro getting doctors
and health professionals

00:15:11.371 --> 00:15:13.870
to start thinking about this
as part of the paradigm of what

00:15:13.870 --> 00:15:16.040
they do when they see people.

00:15:16.040 --> 00:15:18.230
Now part of what I
do is to keep people

00:15:18.230 --> 00:15:19.482
from doing stupid things.

00:15:19.482 --> 00:15:21.440
So if you show up in my
office and you're like,

00:15:21.440 --> 00:15:24.300
I'm on the Google Running
