00:16:49.870 --> 00:16:52.930
and I think goal setting
is a big piece of that

00:16:52.930 --> 00:16:55.520
as well as some of the stuff
to think about in terms

00:16:55.520 --> 00:16:56.970
of what you want to do.

00:16:56.970 --> 00:17:00.730
And the goal is to basically
die young as late as possible.

00:17:00.730 --> 00:17:03.670
I made the comment before
about fitness versus fatness.

00:17:03.670 --> 00:17:07.339
And again, I would much rather
you be overweight and active

00:17:07.339 --> 00:17:08.660
than skinny and inactive.

00:17:08.660 --> 00:17:11.030
The benefits of
health and exercise

00:17:11.030 --> 00:17:14.760
kick in not with your
body shape or size.

00:17:14.760 --> 00:17:16.339
It has to do with
what you're doing.

00:17:16.339 --> 00:17:19.390
And so it's better be fat and
fit than skinny and unfit.

00:17:19.390 --> 00:17:22.140
Low levels of fitness is
a much bigger risk factor

00:17:22.140 --> 00:17:23.109
than it is activity.

00:17:23.109 --> 00:17:25.607
So it's what you're doing
that becomes the key thing.

00:17:25.607 --> 00:17:27.940
And you're going to be hearing
a lot more of this coming

00:17:27.940 --> 00:17:30.720
up in the next five years or so,
something called interleukin 6.

00:17:30.720 --> 00:17:33.719
So interleukins basically
tell cells what to do.

00:17:33.719 --> 00:17:35.260
They're kind of like
the quarterbacks

00:17:35.260 --> 00:17:37.510
of telling different
cells what to do.

00:17:37.510 --> 00:17:40.350
Interleukin 6 is
made in two places.

00:17:40.350 --> 00:17:42.600
It's made in your muscles,
and it's made in your fats.

00:17:42.600 --> 00:17:45.400
If you're sitting around
not doing anything,

00:17:45.400 --> 00:17:48.750
your fat makes IL-6, which
is pro-inflammatory so pretty

00:17:48.750 --> 00:17:53.536
much every chronic disease
we see, asthma, arthritis,

00:17:53.536 --> 00:17:55.160
you name it, most
every chronic disease

00:17:55.160 --> 00:17:58.250
is affected by levels of
circulating inflammation.

00:17:58.250 --> 00:18:01.339
And when you're making this fat
IL-6, it's a pro-inflammatory.

00:18:01.339 --> 00:18:03.130
So you basically get
these increased levels

00:18:03.130 --> 00:18:06.030
of different markers of
general body inflammation.

00:18:06.030 --> 00:18:09.190
When IL-6 is made by muscle, it
has the exact opposite effect.

00:18:09.190 --> 00:18:11.820
It basically is completely
anti-inflammatory.

00:18:11.820 --> 00:18:15.610
So the idea here is that
chronic disease is basically

00:18:15.610 --> 00:18:19.280
prevented and treated with
higher circulating IL-6

00:18:19.280 --> 00:18:20.600
from muscle.

00:18:20.600 --> 00:18:23.140
And so we're just discovering
this and applying this.

00:18:23.140 --> 00:18:27.300
That's why things like colon
cancer or things that might not

00:18:27.300 --> 00:18:29.900
make a lot of sense-- why would
I exercise and that would help

00:18:29.900 --> 00:18:32.566
that?-- I think there's a lot of
chronic disease models that are

00:18:32.566 --> 00:18:35.059
to be affected by this concept
of IL-6 as we go forth.

00:18:35.059 --> 00:18:37.100
You'll hear more about
this in the years to come.

00:18:37.100 --> 00:18:38.683
But it's a super
interesting, I think,

00:18:38.683 --> 00:18:41.000
field that we're
just recognizing

00:18:41.000 --> 00:18:43.230
the benefits of this
beyond the scope of it just

00:18:43.230 --> 00:18:45.021
makes me feel good.

