00:20:26.390 --> 00:20:30.300
And as you do that, you're just
basically burning calories.

00:20:30.300 --> 00:20:32.500
What that does is think
about that first slide

00:20:32.500 --> 00:20:34.410
I showed you from that
journal "Circulation."

00:20:34.410 --> 00:20:38.190
You're reducing your
risk of chronic disease.

00:20:38.190 --> 00:20:39.330
I think of it this way.

00:20:39.330 --> 00:20:41.820
Basically, we had this
huge public health campaign

00:20:41.820 --> 00:20:43.840
against smoking, because
smoking was correlated

00:20:43.840 --> 00:20:46.230
to all kinds of things,
heart disease, diabetes,

00:20:46.230 --> 00:20:47.950
certain types of cancer.

00:20:47.950 --> 00:20:49.855
Sitting is a new smoking.

00:20:49.855 --> 00:20:50.577
All right?

00:20:50.577 --> 00:20:52.160
Straight up, sitting
is a new smoking.

00:20:52.160 --> 00:20:55.070
Inactivity and the health
problems from inactivity

00:20:55.070 --> 00:20:56.880
are almost identical
to the health problems

00:20:56.880 --> 00:20:59.780
from smoking,
which is why I want

00:20:59.780 --> 00:21:01.996
to get going on public
health campaigns

00:21:01.996 --> 00:21:03.870
to encourage activity
much in the way we used

00:21:03.870 --> 00:21:06.390
those same things to get
rid of many of the smokers

00:21:06.390 --> 00:21:10.190
we used to see, because the
profiles are almost identical.

00:21:10.190 --> 00:21:11.990
Silver workouters,
we have to start

00:21:11.990 --> 00:21:14.010
thinking about increasing
your kinetic chain.

00:21:14.010 --> 00:21:15.468
And then golds are
