00:31:58.220 --> 00:32:00.800
And then it's
impossible to recover

00:32:00.800 --> 00:32:02.330
for the rest of the day.

00:32:02.330 --> 00:32:05.700
Is it because you should not
be exercising at that intensity

00:32:05.700 --> 00:32:06.550
for so long?

00:32:06.550 --> 00:32:08.650
Or are there other
things that you

00:32:08.650 --> 00:32:12.535
can do so-- I can sustain
it, but I'm a disaster.

00:32:12.535 --> 00:32:14.660
DR. JORDAN METZL: It's a
great physiology question.

00:32:14.660 --> 00:32:16.486
So what you're
telling me, though you

00:32:16.486 --> 00:32:18.110
don't know you're
telling me, is you're

00:32:18.110 --> 00:32:20.100
finding your lactate threshold.

00:32:20.100 --> 00:32:21.710
So let me give you two terms.

00:32:21.710 --> 00:32:23.590
One is called VO2 Max.

00:32:23.590 --> 00:32:26.220
And so VO2 Max is the
maximum amount of oxygen

00:32:26.220 --> 00:32:28.319
you can take out of your blood.

00:32:28.319 --> 00:32:29.860
And so that's why
if you're at a race

00:32:29.860 --> 00:32:31.985
and there's some woman
ahead of you and you're like

00:32:31.985 --> 00:32:34.150
I want to catch her but
I just can't catch her,

00:32:34.150 --> 00:32:37.240
and every race she's
ahead of you by whatever,

00:32:37.240 --> 00:32:40.907
she physiologically probably
has a better VO2 Max.

00:32:40.907 --> 00:32:43.240
Basically, the more oxygen
you take in, the more ATP you

00:32:43.240 --> 00:32:44.990
can use, the better
your muscle will work.

00:32:44.990 --> 00:32:47.920
And that tends to be
genetic more than anything,

00:32:47.920 --> 00:32:49.210
which is what I always say.

00:32:49.210 --> 00:32:50.990
You can marry whoever
you want, but if you

00:32:50.990 --> 00:32:53.970
want to have fast progeny you
should reproduce with somebody

00:32:53.970 --> 00:32:56.950
who's got a high VO2 Max
is my general comment.

00:32:56.950 --> 00:32:58.550
Now that being
said-- that's a joke.

00:32:58.550 --> 00:33:02.670
All right-- the key that
you're not recognizing

00:33:02.670 --> 00:33:04.650
is what's called your
lactate threshold.

00:33:04.650 --> 00:33:06.430
So lactate threshold
is the level

00:33:06.430 --> 00:33:08.810
where lactic acid builds up
and starts to basically make

00:33:08.810 --> 00:33:12.010
muscles acidic and not work
very well and unpleasant to do

00:33:12.010 --> 00:33:12.510
stuff.

00:33:12.510 --> 00:33:13.134
AUDIENCE: Yeah.

00:33:13.134 --> 00:33:15.510
DR. JORDAN METZL: Lactate
threshold is hugely trainable.

00:33:15.510 --> 00:33:16.606
VO2 Max is not.

00:33:16.606 --> 00:33:17.480
Lactate threshold is.

00:33:17.480 --> 00:33:19.520
So you can go for
longer periods of time

00:33:19.520 --> 00:33:22.670
and not feel like you just
got shot the rest of the day

00:33:22.670 --> 00:33:24.170
if you train your
lactate threshold.

00:33:24.170 --> 00:33:24.890
How do I do that?

00:33:24.890 --> 00:33:26.681
And that is interval
training, so the stuff

00:33:26.681 --> 00:33:27.560
